
## Developer Environment Setup Documentation

### Step-by-Step Instructions

#### 1. Selecting and Installing Windows 11

1. Go to the [Windows 11 download page](https://www.microsoft.com/software-download/windows11).
2. Click on the "Download Now" button to get the Installation Assistant.
3. Run the Installation Assistant and follow the on-screen instructions to upgrade your system to Windows 11.
4. Restart your computer to complete the installation.

#### 2. Installing Visual Studio Code

1. Visit the [Visual Studio Code download page](https://code.visualstudio.com/Download).
2. Choose the version appropriate for your operating system and download it.
3. Run the installer and follow the prompts to complete the installation.
4. Launch Visual Studio Code and customize settings according to your preferences.

#### 3. Setting Up Version Control

**Install Git:**
1. Download Git from [Git-SCM](https://git-scm.com/downloads).
2. Run the installer and follow the prompts, leaving default settings as is.

**Configure Git:**
1. Open Git Bash.
2. Set your username and email:
   ```bash
   git config --global user.name "Your Name"
   git config --global user.email "your.email@example.com"
   ```

**Create a GitHub Account:**
1. Sign up at [GitHub](https://github.com).

**Initialize a Git Repository:**
1. Create a new project directory:
   ```bash
   mkdir my_project
   cd my_project
   ```
2. Initialize Git:
   ```bash
   git init
   ```
3. Make your first commit:
   ```bash
   echo "# My Project" > README.md
   git add README.md
   git commit -m "Initial commit"
   ```

#### 4. Installing Python

1. Download Python from [Python.org](http://www.python.org).
2. Run the installer and ensure you check the option to add Python to PATH.
3. Verify the installation:
   ```bash
   python --version
   pip --version
   ```

#### 5. Installing MySQL

1. Download MySQL Installer from the [MySQL download page](https://dev.mysql.com/downloads/windows/installer/5.7.html).
2. Run the installer and follow the instructions to set up MySQL on your machine.
3. During the setup, create a root password and configure other necessary settings.

#### 6. Optional: Setting Up Docker

1. Download Docker Desktop from [Docker](https://www.docker.com/products/docker-desktop).
2. Run the installer and follow the instructions to set up Docker on your machine.
3. Verify the installation:
   ```bash
   docker --version
   ```

#### 7. Exploring Extensions and Plugins for VS Code

1. Open Visual Studio Code.
2. Go to the Extensions view by clicking on the Extensions icon in the Activity Bar on the side of the window.
3. Search for and install the following extensions:
   - Python
   - GitLens
   - Docker
   - ESLint



